📌 PROJECT TITLE
Real-Time Ground Water Resources Evaluation Using DWLR Data

🎯 OBJECTIVE
Monitor and evaluate groundwater resources in real time using
Digital Water Level Recorder (DWLR) data for efficient water
resource management and conservation.

🚨 PROBLEM STATEMENT
Traditional groundwater monitoring is manual, time-consuming,
and lacks real-time insights. An automated system is required
to continuously track groundwater levels and support
data-driven decision making.

⚙️ MODULES

🔐 Module 1: User Management
• Admin Login
• User Authentication
• Access Control

📡 Module 2: DWLR Data Collection
• Sensor Data Acquisition
• Database Storage

📊 Module 3: Real-Time Monitoring
• Live Water Level Tracking
• Continuous Monitoring

📈 Module 4: Data Analysis
• Trend Analysis
• Historical Data Evaluation

🚨 Module 5: Reports & Alerts
• Automated Reports
• Critical Level Notifications

💻 TECHNOLOGY STACK

🎨 Front End      : HTML, CSS, Bootstrap, React.js
⚡ Back End       : Java, Spring Boot
🗄️ Database       : MySQL
🔧 Technologies   : DWLR Sensors, IoT, GIS Mapping,
                    Analytics Dashboard

🧠 ALGORITHM
Time Series Analysis

✅ EXPECTED OUTCOME
Provides accurate real-time groundwater monitoring,
trend analysis, and alert generation to support
sustainable groundwater management and conservation.

🌍 "Smart Monitoring for Sustainable Water Resources"
